						               													<description>&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#181;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#164;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#172;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#179;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#136;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#187;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#149;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#161;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#179;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#136;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#160; (Psylent Phantom) is a Japanese card game. Players are psychics, trapped by organisations and forced to work as assassins, trying to destroy their targets, other psychic assassins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The assassin has two methods: the Resonance Ring, or the assassin's super powers. You may choose two out of six abilities at the start: lightning, heat, emotion, fate, space, spirit. If you can use your powers to damage the target, they die when they run out of life points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To use the Resonance Ring, you must detect the opponent's two abilities and destroy them with a single blow, by releasing the matched wave from the ring.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Do you want to use your abilities actively or conceal your abilities by bluffing and deflection, and aim for a blow with the ring? You make the decision.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;With three or four players, your target is the player to your left.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;With only three actions, attack, pass, or use the ring, players must choose different strategies. Players that are aggressive and attacking, risk being destroyed with a single blow from a ring. This keeps the game uncertain and tense.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
